# ZIndex

ZIndex component is a basic and simple component that would wrap around any other component which deals with portal and requires
zIndex manipulations. The main purpose of this component is to effectively manage zIndex calculations as and when components are
mounted or unmounted.

## Installation & Import

```bash
yarn add @ids-ts/zindex
```

```tsx
import { ZIndex } from '@ids-ts/zindex';
```

## Props API

| Prop | Type | Required | Description |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| `assignZIndex` | `boolean` | No | - |
| `children` | `React.ReactElement` | Yes | - |
| `disableZIndex` | `boolean` | No | - |
| `style` | `React.CSSProperties` | No | - |
| `incrementBaseZIndex` | `() => void` | No | - |
| `decrementBaseZIndex` | `() => void` | No | - |
| `getCurrentBaseZIndex` | `() => number` | No | * Getter method to get topZIndex for the component from the Context. |

<details>
<summary>Full TypeScript Interface</summary>

```typescript
export interface ZIndexProps {
  /**
   * Flag to indicate if or not to assign z-index.
   *
   * @default false
   */
  assignZIndex?: boolean;
  /**
   * Children node may be actual components or portal that the ZIndex component
   * would wrap.
   */
  children: React.ReactElement;
  /**
   * Flag to indicate if or not we need to disabled zIndex or if component wants to
   * handle zIndex by itself.
   *
   * @default false
   */
  disableZIndex?: boolean;
  /**
   * Style object to cascade
   *
   * @default {}
   */
  style?: React.CSSProperties;
  /**
   * Method to increment topZIndex for the component. ZIndex would call this method
   * to update when a component needs to be mounted and needed higher zIndex.
   */
  incrementBaseZIndex?: () => void;
  /**
   * Method to decrement topZIndex for the component. ZIndex would call this method
   * to update when a component is unmounted and we need to reset the zIndex applied.
   */
  decrementBaseZIndex?: () => void;
  /**
   * Getter method to get topZIndex for the component from the Context.
   */
  getCurrentBaseZIndex?: () => number;
}
```

</details>

